I"[<p>Up until Matlab 2013b, one could modify the C/C++ mex compilation flags by editing the <code class="highlighter-rouge">mexopts.sh</code> file, usually found in <code class="highlighter-rouge">~/.matlab/mexopts.sh</code>. A common example nowadays is adding the <code class="highlighter-rouge">-std=c++11</code> option to compile C++ code from the C++11 standard (<a href="http://www.codeproject.com/Articles/570638/Ten-Cplusplus-Features-Every-Cplusplus-Developer">which has some awesome features</a>). To do that in Matlab 2013 and below, you would simply add the flag to the CXXFLAGS variable.</p>
